content.title: Kanban Slots
content.visibleText:
Jigsaw (1 slot)
1 commit defense goal - delivered, release made available to customers with 4 customers requesting access to date
1 stretch defense goal: canceled in agreement with the BU after reassessing its value
4 new defense goals were added mid-quarter: 2 already delivered, 1 pending completion by EoQ2 and the 4th blocked on the customer side

content.title: Commit: Upgrade Messenger to Java 11, fix two vulnerabilities, support new goals
content.visibleText:
After we completed the migration of Messenger to Java 11 in April, and then shifted our focus to Aurea Monitor's top customers:
Lufthansa failed the PCI audit due to security issues with Monitor - this is now fixed
SoftwareAG was blocked from upgrading its white-label product because the interceptor did not support Java 11. We have released a version that will enable that upgrade.

content.title: NEW goal: Monitor: Upgrade Webmethods Interceptor to version 10.15 (Java 11)
content.visibleText:
BLOCKED
Risk: SoftwareAG must provide installation and use case instructions to enable us to prepare the environment with their tools and test the upgrade. This step is impossible to avoid as we build software that connects with third-party tools. Action: We are pushing them to provide the necessary licenses and information to unblock this activity.

content.title: Messenger Java 17 upgrade
content.visibleText:
Messenger Java 17 was added to the Q2 objective as we over-delivered on the other business objectives.
This is not simply complying Messenger with Java 17 but understanding the inter container communication infrastructure and providing supported solutions. We are derisking this activity to ensure the Messenger architecture will cope with Java 17 changes or if we need to redesign core parts of the system.

content.title: Overall Reflection
content.visibleText:
We continue simplifying the deliverables while maintaining the business objective. This enabled us to overdeliver and extend the number of business objectives winning quarter for the second month in a row.
We must provide all improvements done in the products to the Renewals team so they can start the discussion based on these deliverables.
